text: My Sister Eileen is an American sitcom that aired CBS from October 5, 1960 to April 12, 1961 for one season and 26 episodes. It stars Elaine Stritch, Shirley Bonne, Jack Weston, Rose Marie, Raymond Bailey, Stubby Kaye, Agnes Moorehead and was based on the autobiographical short stories by Ruth McKenney. ==Other websites== * Category:1960 television series debuts Category:1961 television series endings Category:1960s American comedy television series Category:CBS network shows Category:English-language television programs
